# Advanced Features Demonstration Script
new-tournament GrandSlam football
add-stage round-robin Groups
# Use set-policy to change the standings to knockout-progression in DRAFT state
set-policy Groups standings knockout-progression

# Create custom teams
create-team AllStars
add-player AllStars P1 GOALKEEPER 1
add-player AllStars P2 DEFENDER 2
add-player AllStars P3 DEFENDER 3
add-player AllStars P4 DEFENDER 4
add-player AllStars P5 DEFENDER 5
add-player AllStars P6 MIDFIELDER 6
add-player AllStars P7 MIDFIELDER 7
add-player AllStars P8 MIDFIELDER 8
add-player AllStars P9 FORWARD 9
add-player AllStars P10 FORWARD 10
add-player AllStars P11 FORWARD 11
add-player AllStars Bench12 FORWARD 12
register AllStars

# Register auto-generated team
register Opponents
close-registration
publish

# Show team to see roster
show team AllStars

start-tournament
start-match next

# Score by specific player P9
action goal AllStars P9 15

# Opponent scores
action goal Opponents 30

# Substitute P9 for Bench12
substitute AllStars P9 Bench12 40

# VAR rules the opponent's goal offside! Wait, we need the action ID.
# Since we don't know the generated ID in a script, we'll demonstrate a statistical action instead.
# (Revoke requires a UUID, so it's hard to script blindly unless we guess the ID or the engine has a 'last' shortcut, but we'll show statistical actions).
action offside Opponents 42

# Injury to P10!
injury AllStars P10 2 "Broken Toe" 44

finish-period

# Show match details at half time
show match

# Second half
action foul AllStars P2 50
action yellow AllStars P2 51

# Disqualify the opponent!
disqualify Opponents

finish-period

# The match is over (or ended early by walkover depending on engine).
# Show matches to see the walkover status
show matches

advance-stage
show standings
quit
